pageContext.description: Blade has central rib and, apparently, bevelled edge. Flanges continue somewhat beyond stop-ridge. Much corroded; blade broken through and mended; one corner of cutting edge broken off.
pageContext.other: 3 quite well drawn pictures of palstave on reverse.,Flanges quite decayed, more on one side than other.,Edge crescent-shaped.
pageContext.collection: London Museum 59.31,Given by City Museum, Bristol, where numbered E.457, April 1959.,Acquired by Bristol Museum from J.E. Pritchard, 1913.
pageContext.site: greater london,(middlesex),neasden,said to have been found 1905
